title.description: The title for a popup with buttons for different reading portions. Ex. Genesis 1-3, 1 Chronicles 1:1-3

createSchedule.description: Title for a popup for reading schedule creation.

readingPortionDescPhld.description: Title of the selection input for reading portions description. Below this title they have the input for selecting Article, Chapter, Page, or typing their own description.

article.description: A preset reading portion description for creating a custom schedule based on a publication. If chosen, the user will read a certain amount of ARTICLEs in a publication each day.

chapter.description: A preset reading portion description for creating a custom schedule based on a publication. If chosen, the user will read a certain amount of CHAPTERs in a publication each day.

page.description: A preset reading portion description for creating a custom schedule based on a publication. If chosen, the user will read a certain amount of PAGEs in a publication each day.

paragraph.description: A preset reading portion description for creating a custom schedule based on a publication. If chosen, the user will read a certain amount of PARAGRAPHs in a publication each day.

title.description: TITLE of an input field for selecting the type of reading portion they would like to use in their custom schedule for a publication. (Article, Page, Chapter, etc.)

numberOfPortions.description: TITLE for a custom schedule creation popup input field. The user will input how many portions (Articles, Chapters, Pages, etc.) are in the publication they are making the schedule for.

numberOfPortionsPhld.description: DESCRIPTION for a custom schedule creation popup input field where the user will input how many portions (Articles, Chapters, Pages, etc.) are in the publication they are making the schedule for.

portionsPerDay.description: TITLE for an input where the user will decide how many Articles, Chapters, Pages, etc. they would like to read each day for their schedule.

portionsPerDayPhld.description: DESCRIPTION for an input where the user will decide how many Articles, Chapters, Pages, etc. they would like to read each day for their schedule.
portionsPerDayPhld.value: How many {{portionDesc}}s to read each day

startingPortion.description: TITLE for an input field where the user will decide which Article, Page, etc. that they will start their schedule from.

startingPortionPhld.description: DESCRIPTION for an input field where the user will decide which Article, Page, etc. that they will start their schedule from.
startingPortionPhld.value: {{portionDesc}} you would like to start from

scheduleName.description: TITLE for an input where the user will decide the name they would like to have as the display for their reading schedule.

scheduleDuration.description: TITLE for an input where the user will decide how many years their reading schedule will last for. If they choose 1, then they will finish reading the whole bible 1 year from the creation of the schedule.

scheduleDurPhld.description: DESCRIPTION for an input where the user will decide how many years their reading schedule will last for. If they choose 1, then they will finish reading the whole bible 1 year from the creation of the schedule.
scheduleDurPhld.value: How many years the schedule should last from start to finish?

shouldTrack.description: TITLE for a check box. If checked, the schedule will keep track of the date that each reading portion should be completed. If unchecked it will not display any dates or go out of date.

startingVerse.description: TITLE for a set of inputs where the user can decide which verse of the bible to start their reading schedule from.

unfinished.description: A warning that will be displayed to the user if they do not fill out all of the required values in the create schedule popup, or they have used incorrect values
unfinished.value: Please fill in all of the required fields with valid values to make a schedule

about.description: DESCRIPTION for an approximate date. This one indicates that the event most likely took place sometime near a certain year(Ex. About 539 B.C.E.) See link below for examples. See explanation of 'a.' 'c.' and 'b.' at bottom of page.

after.description: DESCRIPTION for an approximate date. This one indicates that the event definitely took place after a certain year (Ex. After 539 B.C.E.) See link below for examples. See explanation of 'a.' 'c.' and 'b.' at bottom of page.

before.description: DESCRIPTION for an approximate date. This one indicates that the event definitely took place before a certain year (Ex. Before 539 B.C.E.) See link below for examples. See explanation of 'a.' 'c.' and 'b.' at bottom of page.

approxDate.description: Ordering for a description of a date. For instance with use in dates of events in the bible, or when bible books were written. You can go to the link below and change the language to your translation language to see examples. (Ex. After 607 B.C.E, Before 30 C.E.)

bce.description: Indicator for an ancient date. (Ex. 539 B.C.E)

ce.description: Indicator for an ancient date. (Ex. 98 C.E)

ancientDate.description: The ordering of an ancient date's format. (Ex. 539 B.C.E. or 98 C.E.)

dateSpan.description: Format for a span of dates. (Ex. 607 B.C.E - 537 B.C.E.)

8.value: 11 Years of Judges rule from about {{startYear}} to {{endYear}}

emptyList.description: Text that will be displayed if there are no more reading items on the home page
emptyList.value: You have no more readings for the day

baseTitle.description: A title for a notification reminding the user to do their reading today

bigText.description: Text that will show up on a notification
bigText.value: Let's see what you have left to do today

message.description: Small text that will show up on a notification

notificationName.description: LABEL for an input field where the user will input the name to be displayed for a notification they are creating

notificationPopupTitle.description: TITLE for the popup used to create a new notification

deleteNotificationMessage.description: A warning that will show up so that the user can confirm whether or not they truly want to delete the notification they selected to delete.
deleteNotificationMessage.value: Are you sure you want to delete "{{notificationName}}" notification?

openJWLibrary.description: Text that will appear on a button. When the user presses this button it will open the JW Library application.

0.description: The typical ordinal value for numbers ending with "0" (Ex. 10th, 20th, 30th, etc.). This does not include special cases. See below for special cases.

1.description: The typical ordinal value for numbers ending with "1" (Ex. 1st, 21st, 31st, etc.). This does not include special cases. See below for special cases.

2.description: The typical ordinal value for numbers ending with "2" (Ex. 2nd, 22nd, 32nd, etc.). This does not include special cases. See below for special cases.

3.description: The typical ordinal value for numbers ending with "3" (Ex. 3rd, 23rd, 33rd, etc.). This does not include special cases. See below for special cases.

4.description: The typical ordinal value for numbers ending with "4" (Ex. 4th, 14th, 24th, etc.). This does not include special cases. See below for special cases.

5.description: The typical ordinal value for numbers ending with "5" (Ex. 5th, 15th, 25th, etc.). This does not include special cases. See below for special cases.

6.description: The typical ordinal value for numbers ending with "6" (Ex. 6th, 16th, 26th, etc.). This does not include special cases. See below for special cases.

7.description: The typical ordinal value for numbers ending with "7" (Ex. 7th, 17th, 27th, etc.). This does not include special cases. See below for special cases.

8.description: The typical ordinal value for numbers ending with "8" (Ex. 8th, 18th, 28th, etc.). This does not include special cases. See below for special cases.

9.description: The typical ordinal value for numbers ending with "9" (Ex. 9th, 19th, 29th, etc.). This does not include special cases. See below for special cases.

setNotification.description: A LABEL for an input field where the user will decide what time of day they would like their notification to reset at.

nameTaken.description: A warning which will pop up if the user picks a name for a schedule, reminder, notification, etc which they have already used.
nameTaken.value: Please select a name you haven't used

readingReminders.description: A TITLE for a popup which contains reminders for a user before they start reading.

body2-8.description: A paragraph for the reading reminders popup. (See link below for source material)

readingInfo.description: TITLE for a popup which will show information about the currently selected reading portion. It will display the year and where the bible book, who wrote it, etc.

readingPortion.description: LABEL for a string of text that describes the reading portion. (Ex. Genesis 1-3)

timeCovered.description: LABEL for a string of text which will say the time covered for the reading portion or bible book

whereWritten.description: LABEL for a string of text which will say where the bible book for the current reading portion was written.

whenWritten.description: LABEL for a string of text which will say when the bible book for the current reading portion was written.

writers.description: LABEL for a string of text which will say who wrote the current portion of the Bible related to the user's reading.

readingSchedules.description: Text to be a title for a page of reading schedules

completeReminderMessage.description: A message that will appear when a user clicks on a reminder on the home page asking them to confirm that they wish to mark it completed

dailyReading.description: Will be a title for a reminder

dailyText.description: A preset reminder that will be created automatically for the user which they can turn on to remind them daily to read their daily text from examining the scriptures daily.

midweekMeetingStudy.description: A preset reminder that will be created automatically for the user which they can turn on to remind them weekly on a certain day to complete their midweek meeting study.

reminder.description: Description of what a reminder is. Could be used as a title for reminders so that users know where to go to adjust them

weekendMeetingStudy.description: A preset reminder that will be created automatically for the user which they can turn on to remind them weekly on a certain day to complete their weekend meeting study.

title.description: A title to describe what the schedule is. A weekly reading schedule. It is based off of the reading schedule for the current week according to the life and ministry meeting workbook.

showDaily.description: LABEL for a toggle/checkbox where a user can decide whether they want each individual day of the weekly reading to show on their home page or just the weekly reading button.
showDaily.value: Show daily portion of weekly reading

daily.description: A selection value to be used for items that the user wants to repeat every DAY

weekly.description: A selection value to be used for items that the user wants to repeat every WEEK

monthly.description: A selection value to be used for items that the user wants to repeat every MONTH

never.description: A selection value to be used for items that the user wants to NEVER repeat

completed.description: A label for a checkbox which describes whether a certain reminder was completed according to when it is set to reset "Completed (this month, this week, today)"

deleteReminderMessage.description: A message which will show up in a popup asking the user to confirm deleting the selected reminder on the reminders page

every.description: A LABEL for an input where the user can decide when they would like their reminder to reset. (Ex. Every: 1 st of the month for a monthly schedule, Every Tuesday for a weekly schedule, etc.)

name.description: LABEL for an input field where the user can input the name they would like to have displayed for the reminder they are creating or have already created.

reminderPopupTitle.description: TITLE for a popup in which the user can create a new reminder that will show up like a reading portion on their home screen.

repeats.description: LABEL for a selection input where the user can select how frequently they would like their reminder to repeat. Daily, Weekly, Monthly, Never.

title.description: TITLE for the page where a user can manage and create reminders.

schedules.description: Title for the Schedules page which lists all of the reading schedules a user has created

deleteScheduleMessage.description: A warning message that will appear when a user tries to delete a reading schedule they have created to make sure they really want to delete it.
deleteScheduleMessage.value: Are you sure you want to delete "{{scheduleName}}" schedule?

hideCompleted.description: LABEL for a checkbox the user can click which will hide all reading portions which are already completed

adjustedVersePrompt.description: A warning message to let the user know that the start verse they tried to use in schedule creation is not a real verse, therefore their schedule was adjusted to start from the nearest verse.
adjustedVersePrompt.value: Adjusted start verse from "{{initialBibleBook}} {{initialChapter}}:{{initialVerse}}" to "{{startBibleBook}} {{startChapter}}:{{startVerse}}" because initial request was out of bounds.

scheduleType.description: LABEL to explain what the buttons below are referring to, different reading orders or types they can use to create their schedule.

sequential.description: TITLE on a button the user can press to proceed with creating a sequential schedule.

sequentialDescription.description: DESCRIPTION of what a sequential schedule is.
sequentialDescription.value: Read the bible from Genesis to Revelation

chronological.description: TITLE on a button the user can press to proceed with creating a chronological schedule.

chronologicalDescription.description: DESCRIPTION of what a chronological schedule is.
chronologicalDescription.value: Read the bible in the order in which events occurred. (EXPERIMENTAL: If you find a discrepency please contact me)

thematic.description: TITLE on a button the user can press to proceed with creating a thematic schedule.

thematicDescription.description: DESCRIPTION of what a thematic schedule is.
thematicDescription.value: Each day, read from a different section of the Bible in a weekly cycle: Day 1 - The Law, 2 - History, 3 - Psalms, 4 - Poetry, 5 - Prophecy, 6 - Gospels, 7 - Letters

custom.description: TITLE on a button the user can press to proceed with creating a custom schedule.

customDescription.description: DESCRIPTION of what a custom schedule is and what will proceed if the user presses this button.
customDescription.value: Create a custom schedule for a publication

weeklyReadingResetDay.description: LABEL for an input where the user can set which day of the week they would like their weekly reading from the midweek meeting to reset. Usually the day after the midweek meeting.

about.description: The title for a button on the settings page which will link to this website

contact.description: The title for a button on the settings page which will link to sending an email to the developer

version.description: The title for a section on the settings page which will display the current version of the app they have installed (Ex. 1.7.3)

today.description: A LABEL for the home page for reading items that are to be read during the current day. (Today, This Week, This Month, Other)

thisWeek.description: A LABEL for the home page for reading items that are to be read during the current week. (Today, This Week, This Month, Other)

thisMonth.description: A LABEL for the home page for reading items that are to be read during the current month. (Today, This Week, This Month, Other)

other.description: A LABEL for the home page for reading items that do not track their completion date. (Today, This Week, This Month, Other)

chapterAbrev.description: An abbreviated form of the word chapter. Something one or 2 characters long.

verseAbrev.description: An abbreviated form of the word verse. Something one or 2 characters long.

warning.description: Usually will be a title of a popup with a warning message

name.description: The long form for Sunday.
The long form for Monday.
The long form for Tuesday.
The long form for Wednesday.
The long form for Thursday.
The long form for Friday.
The long form for Saturday.
